  "comment_text": {
    "sn9.6:1.2": "Penelope (<i lang='pi' translate='no'>jālinī</i>) means “weaver”, and is used as a term for the craving that binds beings in transmigration (eg. <a href='https://suttacentral.net/an4.199/en/sujato'>AN 4.199</a>). Compare <i lang='pi' translate='no'>tantrāyī</i> at Śatapatha Brāhmaṇa 14.2.2.22. ",
    "sn9.6:3.4": "Per Bodhi”s <em>Connected Discourses</em>, adopt reading <i lang='pi' translate='no'>devakaññābhisattikā</i> found in a Sinhala-script manuscript cited in the PTS edition. "
  },
